{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":44736,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-28T15:02:02.730Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWe‚Äôre seeing ShadowMap Coverage being skewed to the Left (in the direction that the Directional Light is pointing) in the below screenshot.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe‚Äôre not doing anything unusual that we know of here.   This error does not happen in the Samples, so not sure why it‚Äôs happening in our particular scene.   In this case, the ShadowMap is skewed towards the X-Negative Axis, and away from X-Positive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis shows missing shadows (or partial for the girl) on Right side(X-Positive), but on Left Side (X-negative), the shadows extend very far way.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/eh7fX2dmBSAmWEko9PAJyGYMW7a.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4_2_690x367.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"eh7fX2dmBSAmWEko9PAJyGYMW7a\" width=\"690\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4_2_690x367.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4_2_1035x550.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4_2_1380x734.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e2001√ó1066 344 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt skews the coverage in the direction of the Scene‚Äôs ‚ÄúDirectional Light‚Äù.   For the above screenshot, the directional light direction is:  new Vector3(-1f, -1f, -0.2f)    and the shadow map coverage is strong towards X-Negative.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf we change the Direction Light to ‚Äúnew Vector3(1f, -1f, -0.2f)‚Äù, then it skews the coverage towards X-Positive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSince this does not happen in the ‚ÄúSkeletal Animation‚Äù sample, it‚Äôs definitely some sort of bug with our scene/camera setup.   But I‚Äôm using the same code for this as the Skeletal Animation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDoes anyone have any clues as to where in our setup we should be looking for something that could cause this type of Shadow-Map skew?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-28T15:02:35.208Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":24.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/6/640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"640dc6184f3d70ce00e656555c22db772ea941a4.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44737,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-28T15:06:49.873Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOne thing that might be peculiar about our scene vs. the Samples is ‚ÄúSCALE‚Äù.   These buildings are 2000 units tall here‚Ä¶ so our scale is about 50x larger than that of the Samples.   Perhaps our scale is triggering some sort of buggish behavior here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT ‚Äì NOPE!  I reduced Shadow Map splits down to 10% of what they were, and still this defect persists:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/90RZmfMV4puuanNNDkmusJfwUs2.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa_2_634x500.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"90RZmfMV4puuanNNDkmusJfwUs2\" width=\"634\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa_2_634x500.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa_2_951x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1240√ó977 70.2 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI even then scaled up the Skeletal Demo to 100x size ‚Äì and still IT WORKS.   So there is something else peculiar about our scene setup or camera.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis screenshot shows it working for the Skeletal Demo scene:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/02aeb5e500caee54e70f6a391fb652d3932bacec.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/nJgLRrbkOtdUuKMJj6EhQBwkDq.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/02aeb5e500caee54e70f6a391fb652d3932bacec.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"nJgLRrbkOtdUuKMJj6EhQBwkDq\" width=\"491\" height=\"500\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/02aeb5e500caee54e70f6a391fb652d3932bacec_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e737√ó749 51.3 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-28T15:31:12.882Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":9.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/02aeb5e500caee54e70f6a391fb652d3932bacec.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"02aeb5e500caee54e70f6a391fb652d3932bacec.jpeg","clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/3/3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"3f2cc3e4dd629578bc48c3fd9711a28bb369bffa.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44743,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-04T08:19:47.423Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOK, just discovered that this IS a problem in the Urho Samples project as well.   Check out the top image, where we are looking away from the sun ‚Äì the shadows are cast for very far away models.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/6cdaOgjt7hl1s6zRvgi3eISdSoF.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49_2_690x273.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"6cdaOgjt7hl1s6zRvgi3eISdSoF\" width=\"690\" height=\"273\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49_2_690x273.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49_2_1035x409.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1273√ó504 61.2 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThen I just rotate the camera 180 to look into the sun, and here the models from VERY CLOSE already have lost their shadows!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/iQgJZWyYYoDxHogg2OnSRlMBZbc.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622_2_690x312.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"iQgJZWyYYoDxHogg2OnSRlMBZbc\" width=\"690\" height=\"312\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622_2_690x312.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622_2_1035x468.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1152√ó522 68.9 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis defect is more obvious the lower-in-sky the sun is.   Directional Light going closer to horizontal (casting long shadows), exhibits this defect the most.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo there appears to be a shadow-map-skew bug, that is responding to the Directional Light‚Äôs direction, especially as it goes more horizontal.   I‚Äôd like to see an Urho maintain reproduce this\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNOTE: THIS ONLY HAPPENS WHEN I SCALE UP THE ‚ÄúSkeletalAnimation‚Äù demo up to 100x the original size (scale the plane, the models, the Shadow Clip distances, everything)‚Ä¶ so the scene ‚Äúappears the same‚Äù, but the shadows are messed up, the higher the scale we go.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo this is related to scene Scale.  Higher scales trigger this defect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUrho3D Defect:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe defect is that Shadow-Map get skewed away from the Direction Light, tragically, at higher scale.  This should not be scale-independent.   Scale should have no Visual impact on ShadowMap skew.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-03-04T08:20:47.161Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":13.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/8/840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"840fbc9b5ad1ccb8e968291da7c174a52f63e622.jpeg","clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2b6e73cf4c2f8887a3f1ab5754fa29e065a79d49.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44744,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-04T17:03:39.625Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs another screenshot of the Samples Skeletal Animations, with scale set to 1000x‚Ä¶ here the shadows become super defective as you look towards the light source:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/uuAUI5Jte92GXIOcp2FWNCIjGca.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042_2_690x334.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"uuAUI5Jte92GXIOcp2FWNCIjGca\" width=\"690\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042_2_690x334.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042_2_1035x501.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1189√ó577 209 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWORKAROUND:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe workaround is to more Urho-Standard scale (e.g Camera Far Clip range between 100 to 10,000) ‚Ä¶ but that shouldn‚Äôt be a requirement of Urho3D for using shadows.   Is there some way to adjust the built-in Shadow Map technique to accommodate larger scales?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur game world is 10 million units (meters) side-to-side, but will never allow you to get closer than 1000 units from what you are viewing‚Ä¶   Our workaround fix will be to change our standard unit-of-measure from Meters to Kilometers.   And that‚Äôll resolve this issue for us.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-03-04T18:41:22.151Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":18.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/d/d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"d5b698fa6206f048051df5f17c0e15962b525042.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true},{"id":44745,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-04T17:12:12.040Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eMore notes ‚Äì if I instead scale SkeletalAnimations to 0.1 (making it smaller) - the shadow suffer a different defect - in that the Cascade don‚Äôt seem to really be 1, 5, 20‚Ä¶   The result is blurry/close-up shadows (same as if the Cascade ranges were still more like 10, 50, 200).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/4Cbt4YPR9DgO0DPsHmq8878k7a1.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89_2_690x329.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"4Cbt4YPR9DgO0DPsHmq8878k7a1\" width=\"690\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89_2_690x329.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89_2_1035x493.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1178√ó563 152 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo shadow Cascades of that are too small or too large ‚Äì seem to trigger an Urho defect, in that it doesn‚Äôt really let you set these values outside of some built-in optimum range‚Ä¶  such as 10, 50, 200.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo our workaround is to resize our scene to the ‚ÄúUrho supported scene size‚Äù (with regards to shadows).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-03-04T17:13:10.307Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":19,"readers_count":18,"score":3.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2059b43adde524e2c95475ae4fe2a545ffd7fa89.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44746,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-04T18:43:08.899Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe reason we want our scene scale to remain meters, despite the world map being 10 million meters wide ‚Äì is that we still want to think in terms of meters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDue to this defect of Urho, we‚Äôll be switching our game units to Kilometers, which means that we‚Äôll have human characters that are just ‚Äú0.002‚Äù units tall.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-03-04T18:43:08.899Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":19,"readers_count":18,"score":8.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44747,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-06T03:09:49.735Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou may already be dealing with this, but you‚Äôre probably going to run into other issues if your may is 10^7 character-size units wide. My recollection is that single precision floats have only about a 10^7 precision, so at the edges of the map you‚Äôll run into a bunch of floating point rounding errors because the computer can‚Äôt tell the difference, for example, between 10^7 and 10^7+0.1 (say the width of a characters hand).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you‚Äôre looking for suggestions for how to get around that I have a few (though no idea if they‚Äôre any good), but I don‚Äôt want to impose if you‚Äôve already thought through it. And I also don‚Äôt want to drag the thread too far off topic.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-03-06T03:09:49.735Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":16,"readers_count":15,"score":3.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44748,"name":"","username":"JSandusky","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jsandusky/{size}/3220_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-06T04:51:22.096Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf this is a directional light the problem is probably with how far the directional ‚Äú\u003cem\u003ewalks backward\u003c/em\u003e‚Äù to include things potentially out of view. I can‚Äôt remember where that‚Äôs done though and I might be crossing engines in my memory.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-03-06T04:51:22.096Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":16,"readers_count":15,"score":3.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":7210,"topic_slug":"shadow-map-coverage-skewed-to-the-side","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"fla